  <result type="2">
   <title>
    <narrative xml:lang="EN">Formal steps taken within international fora and reform projects or initiatives launched locally</narrative>
   </title>
   <description>
    <narrative xml:lang="EN">- At national level in pilot economies, understanding of sustainable investment advanced.
- At multilateral level, WTO delegates working on investment facilitation for development.
- At subnational level, improved understanding of division of labour and complementarity between national and subnational efforts in support of sustainable investment. 
- At regional level, non-pilot economies in the region engaged on sustainable investment policies.</narrative>
   </description>
   <reference code="268114" vocabulary="99"></reference>
   <indicator aggregation-status="0" ascending="0" measure="1">
    <title>
     <narrative xml:lang="EN">Formal steps taken within international fora and reform projects or initiatives launched locally</narrative>
    </title>
    <description>
     <narrative xml:lang="EN">- At national level in pilot economies, understanding of sustainable investment advanced.
- At multilateral level, WTO delegates working on investment facilitation for development.
- At subnational level, improved understanding of division of labour and complementarity between national and subnational efforts in support of sustainable investment. 
- At regional level, non-pilot economies in the region engaged on sustainable investment policies.</narrative>
    </description>
    <baseline year="2018">
     <comment>
      <narrative xml:lang="EN">At national level, concept of sustainable investment not well understood in Cambodia and Ghana, and measures not adopted for commercially viable investment to make the maximum contribution to sustainable development. 
At multilateral level, WTO Structured Discussions on Investment Facilitation for Development consider supporting development outcome only through Special and Differential Treatment (SDT), phased-in commitments for developing economies, and technical assistance. Discussions informal in nature and uncertainty over whether these might lead to formal negotiations or a text. 
At subnational level, lack of clarity on how to align national-subnational efforts in support of sustainable investment policies and measures, even as subnational investment institutions proliferating. 
At regional level, unrealized opportunities to use existing frameworks for cooperation on investment facilitation to support sustainable investment policies, frameworks, partnerships, and measures.</narrative>
     </comment>
    </baseline>
    <period>
     <period-start iso-date="2020-01-01"></period-start>
     <period-end iso-date="2020-12-31"></period-end>
